  "elapsed_s": 45.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "In the area there was a woman from one of the gentry families who married a, a Jew and who was invited to the annual New Year's ball, but was told to leave her husband behind.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "That sort of, I would say, symbolizes that level. far as the average Hungarian and the average Jew, who usually was a bearded Jew or at least wore black clothes and certainly, the Hasidim, who wore kaftans and-- was, you know, their contact was limited to the bare essentials.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they really didn't know each other and, for that matter, looked down upon each other for their respective reasons.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And by the time of 1944, the atmosphere was, was charged with animosity that, you know, was the result of, by then, at least 20, 25 years of virulent anti-Semitism practiced by the government to the point where, at times, it was physically dangerous for the Jews or the Jews were in physical danger.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "On Christian holidays, particularly when they had parades, it became very touchy.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But most of all, there was this awareness that they were they, and we were we.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And never the twain shall meet.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So it's a very-- it's a very difficult proposition.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And, you know, the history of, of the Holocaust in Hungary, or the Hungarian aspect of the Holocaust, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] is marked by something very interesting, you know.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We, in the Northeast, were the dispensable Jews.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] Horthy, for instance, more or less considered the Jews of Budapest and the Western part of the country who were more assimilated, more Hungarianized, less strange in their physical appearance.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] He more or less considered those his Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
